<subSubSection id="8E900D626CCD022190DE1E9F9739EB69" type="description">
<paragraph id="B7646C1DA8D665DD7B2B624D6720483C" pageNumber="169">Major: pale to medium yellow; slender; antennal scape just reaching occipital border; occipital border deep, subangulate at midline; pilosity of body dorsum moderately abundant, suberect to erect, and very long; propodeal spine reduced to a denticle; pronotum and all of gaster smooth and shiny.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD3B440C242E883DAC111C94B12E5631" pageNumber="169">Minor: occiput broad and lacking nuchal collar; propodeal spine reduced to a denticle; carinulae limited to circular lines around</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00C4A6F7512095128BFADE8412FAF686" pageNumber="169">antennal fossae; mesopleuron and side of propodeum foveolate and opaque; rest of body smooth and shiny.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BAFD35B9EEAAB095B57BC3A03CACF916" pageNumber="169">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.46, HL 1.62, SL 1.34, EL 0.26, PW 0.72.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="74C511B9A41D3119BDA996E16784F0C0" pageNumber="169">Paratype minor: HW 0.66, HL 0.82, SL 1.16, EL 0.22, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F62655BD0CC4F267E8A487A6B8E331F3" pageNumber="169">color Major: concolorous pale to medium yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6668B7293C9773BC636D2F80BADACC5F" pageNumber="169">Minor: concolorous pale yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
